          "en": "Imam Ja'far al-Sadiq (AS) interprets Quran 23:60, explaining that the 'fear' (wajal) in the hearts of the believers described in this verse stems from a dual spiritual state: they fear that their deeds may be rejected due to disobedience, while simultaneously hoping for divine acceptance. This teaching was given to a student named Ali who asked the Imam directly about the meaning of this Quranic verse.",
